Ray Joe BOLLING v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6328. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Feb. 16, 1960. Joseph P. Jenkins, Kansas City, Kan., for appellant. Paul W. Cress, U. S. Atty., and Jack R. Parr, Asst. U. S. Atty., Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of appellee for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
